                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d677">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51/484a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-06-01T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 1, 1921—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>114. For General Crowder:</p>
                <p>The Department has been advised by representative of certain New York banking
                    interests that bankers are disposed to make the Cuban Government a loan up to
                    $50,000,000 if Cuba desires it. If the Zayas administration desires such a loan
                    as the one mentioned cable the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
